run "node index.js" to retire the first device on the list

it runs functions located in src/index.js to get authorization and such with Alex Joo's login
code in src/casperjs is a casperjs script, not nodejs, which logs in and gets an auth code

secret key, tenant, and app id are created by app registration, all other code won't work if you
register the app in the azure portal, you have to use their new registration site and use a 
non converged app. There's a pretty good chance it changes and everything is ruined
